Rating: 4
This was delicious. I did a few variations though. I used half mint and half basil and added zest from one lime to the dressing. I roasted the salmon (along with lime slices) in the dish for 15 mins at 400 degrees; the marinade became more caramelized and better absorbed in the fish than if I had grilled it. I didn't make the cabbage salad because I had planned a side dish of stir-fried bok choy and shiitake mushrooms, but I would try the salad too in the future. Overall the dressing is very refreshing and I would try it on other dishes like stir fried veggies or grilled shrimp or tofu.

Rating: 4
Best salmon recipe we've ever made. The mint did not sound good so we left it out. Substituted broccoli slaw for the Napa. Added some honey to the reserved marinade and reduced to a syrup drizzled on top when served along with an orzo pasta side. Truly exceptional!

