this has become a staple in our house, it is incredibly delicious. I add chopped peanuts and toasted sesame seeds to the slaw; I also sometimes use red cabbage, and it's very pretty. Truly a groumet easy meal. The marinade works well with chicken, too. Wonderful!

Rating: 2
2.5 forks. This is way too salty if made as directed; the soy sauce takes care of the salt and there's no need to add more. Apart from that, it's nice enough. I added chopped scallions to the slaw and they improved matters. Also took previous reviewers' advice and sauteed the cabbage first, but didn't use butter; I felt that the dairy flavor wasn't quite the thing. I used vegetable oil, with a tiny splash of light sesame oil, and sauteed the cabbage for two minutes, and all was well.

